mob stocking
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:the applying of stock to pasture in heavy numbers to eliminate fern or weeds or to eat out heavy growth in a crop or pasture.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
